TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—On Baluts Algorithm and NP-Completeness for a Chance-Constrained Scheduling Problem
AU  - Kise, Hiroshi
AU  - Ibaraki, Toshihide
Y1  - 1983/03/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.3.384
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.29.3.384
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 384
EP  - 388
VL  - 29
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In 1973, Balut gave an algorithm to solve an n-job one machine scheduling problem in which processing times are random variables and the objective is to minimize the number of tardy jobs with a specified certainty level. This note, however, presents an example for which his algorithm fails to give an optimal schedule. Furthermore, there does not seem to exist any such efficient algorithm because the problem can be shown to be NP-complete.
AB  - In 1973, Balut gave an algorithm to solve an n-job one machine scheduling problem in which processing times are random variables and the objective is to minimize the number of tardy jobs with a specified certainty level. This note, however, presents an example for which his algorithm fails to give an optimal schedule. Furthermore, there does not seem to exist any such efficient algorithm because the problem can be shown to be NP-complete.
